2-8c67-4c26-838b-d12c18df08c4/activity)\n\n\nOutside of OpenSauced, some of the notable projects they contributed to include:\n\n- [Facebook Rapid](https://github.com/facebook/Rapid)\n- [GitHub docs](https://docs.github.com/)\n- [Appwrite Pink](https://github.com/appwrite/pink)\n- [freeCodeCamp](https://github.com/freecodecamp/freecodecamp)\n- [Microsoft autogen](https://github.com/microsoft/autogen)\n\n\nThe `app` repo for OpenSauced, in particular, saw a healthy influx of new and returning contributors. \n\n![break down of app repo](https://dev-to-uploads.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/articles/mkzkxhyf65trlswpf2ta.png)\n\n\u003e To find details about your own project using our pizza CLI, run `npm i -g pizza` in your terminal to install the CLI. Next, run the `pizza show` command with your repo address: `pizza show https://github.com/open-sauced/app`. To find out what other commands you can run and more installation options, check out the [pizza-CLI repo](https://github.com/open-sauced/pizza-cli). \n\n\n## Highlights\nOne of the great parts of seeing our contributors progress through the month was seeing what they were most proud of through their highlights. We had 112 highlights during that time, including blog posts, issues, and PRs. It’s great to be able to share in our contributors' stories. \n\nThrough the highlights, we saw people making their first Hacktoberfest contributions, adding test coverage, working on features, fixing bugs, adding community health files, creating issues to invite a new group of contributors to join in, and more.\n\n[![Issue Highlight](https://dev-to-uploads.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/articles/zyn2s0xi4xngbbl9qwu3.png)](https://app.opensauced.pizza/feed/717)\n\nOne of the best parts of Hacktoberfest is seeing new contributors grow throughout the month and continue to make meaningful contributions. When we started our Hacktoberfest at OpenSauced, we encouraged contributors to [look beyond the green squares](https://dev.to/opensauced/hacktober